profile_positions.description:
VUmc, who has been merged together with AMC and became "Amsterdam UMC", is one of the biggest hospitals within the Netherlands. Their centre offers top-notch care to patients, and are known all over the world for their careful and committed approach to patients, their families and their environment. Their scientific research puts them in the top 3 hospitals worldwide. 

In this critical and important environment, I defined a Roadmap & led the project that upgraded the complete VMware and HPE Hardware stack, for the whole DTAP (Citrix) VDI environment. Which run over 10.000 VDI sessions. In this project we achieved, but is not limited to:

• Upgraded 15 vCenters & vSphere environments from version 5.1 to 6.5u2;
• Upgraded the Complete HPE Stack (HP OneViews, 3PARs, Lefthands, Blade Enclosures, Virtual Connects & Proliant Servers);
• Reduced Storage Usage by almost 70%;
• Designed & Implemented Veeam;
• Designed vROps;
• Created a Life Cycle & Patch Management Plan;
• Security Hardening of the VMware vSphere Environments;
• Defined & Executed Tests Plans for both Functional & Performance tests;
• Improved the overall Infrastructure, without any downtime or business impact.
